    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 2.5",
    "body" : "<p>Try:</p>\n\n<pre><code>v = (float)s / (float)t;\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>Casting the ints to floats will allow floating-point division to take place.</p>\n\n<p>You really only need to cast one, though.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 15939,
      "reputation" : 78503,
      "user_id" : 34218,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/f657c6adf1e623cd6f8818408ecd8f75?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "Jason Coco",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/34218/jason-coco"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 5,
    "last_activity_date" : 1240610033,
    "creation_date" : 1240610033,
    "answer_id" : 787708,
    "question_id" : 787700,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 2.5",
    "body" : "<p>Cast one of the integers to a float to force the operation to be done with floating point math. Otherwise integer math is always preferred. So:</p>\n\n<pre><code>v = (float)s / t;\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
