  "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/questions/787700/how-to-make-the-division-of-2-ints-produce-a-float-instead-of-another-int",
  "title" : "How to make the division of 2 ints produce a float instead of another int?",
  "body" : "<p>In another Bruce Eckels exercise in calculating velocity, <code>v = s / t</code> where s and t are integers.  How do I make it so the division cranks out a float?</p>\n\n<pre><code>class CalcV {\n  float v;\n  float calcV(int s, int t) {\n    v = s / t;\n    return v;\n  } //end calcV\n}\n\npublic class PassObject {\n\n  public static void main (String[] args ) {\n    int distance;\n    distance = 4;\n\n    int t;\n    t = 3;\n\n    float outV;\n\n    CalcV v = new CalcV();\n    outV = v.calcV(distance, t);\n\n    System.out.println(\"velocity : \" + outV);\n  } //end main\n}//end class\n</code></pre>\n"
}